From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 10:31:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Replace Binance OHLCV download with Coinbase Exchange API

- Add fetch_ohlcv(symbol, granularity_seconds, num_candles) hitting the public
  Coinbase /products/{id}/candles endpoint (no auth)
- Handle the 300-candle/request limit via automatic start/end pagination
- Reverse Coinbase's newest-first ordering to chronological before returning
- Aggregate 4h candles from 1h (Coinbase has no native 14400s granularity)
- Retry with exponential backoff (3 attempts) on 429/5xx, raise a clear
  error with symbol+reason on definitive failure
- Keep the existing candle schema (open_time ms, open/high/low/close/volume)
  so signal generation and indicators are untouched
- Leave Binance futures (funding/OI/L-S) endpoints as-is (not OHLCV, out of scope)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
